	</HEAD>
	<body>
		<form id="Form1" method="post" runat="server">
			<TellSafe:LayoutTop ID="ctlLayoutTop" Runat="Server" />
			<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%">
				<TR>
					<TD STYLE="PADDING-RIGHT:100px;PADDING-LEFT:30px;PADDING-TOP:20px">
						<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%">
							<TR>
								<TD VALIGN="top">
									<SPAN CLASS="adH1">TellSafe, LLC Website Privacy Policy</SPAN>
									<BR>
									<BR>
									TellSafe appreciates your confidence in us as a web portal and reporting 
									service. In an attempt to ensure your confidentiality and privacy, we have 
									developed systems to keep your information from outside sources. Encryption of 
									your information using the latest in technology is utilized to help keep your 
									information anonymous and confidential.
									<BR>
									<BR>
									<B>Cookies</B>
									<BR>
									TellSafe does not store cookies (small portions of information about your 
									website use) to gather information about your use of our website. No cookies 
									are stored on your system permanently.
									<BR>
									<BR>
									<B>Automatic Information Storage</B>
									<BR>
									Session Variables may be used temporarily in your system to cache in order to 
									create ease-of-use during your transaction. All Session Variables are deleted 
									when you log off of TellSafe. An example of such information is automatically 
									produced alphanumeric numbers held during your session on our site to 
									facilitate page-to-page transactions. Your name, email, phone, address, company 
									name or otherwise is not stored at any time.
									<BR>
									<BR>
									<B>Partners</B>
									<BR>
									TellSafe does not share your information with partner companies, unless given 
									your express permission in writing. No newsletter or mailing list companies are 
									allowed to access your information including name, address, email, telephone, 
									company name, title, position or otherwise.
									<BR>
									<BR>
									<B>Your Account Access</B>
									<BR>
									Usernames and passwords are stored in our database for use in our reporting 
									system. This information is kept secure on our private servers and is only used 
									to assist you in accessing your account as a client. Reported information is 
									stored only when the one reporting voluntarily gives this information for use 
									by a Subscriber company. No information is released outside of the TellSafe 
									system.
									<BR>
									<BR>
									<B>Terms</B>
									<BR>
									No company other than TellSafe is allowed to access information stored on our 
									servers. Doing so is a violation of the law. TellSafe has placed security 
									measures and firewalls on all network servers in an attempt to prevent outside 
									parties from accessing private information. In the event of a breach of 
									security, TellSafe will press charges to the fullest extent against those 
									parties illegally accessing information from our servers.
								</TD>
							</TR>
						</TABLE>
					</TD>
				</TR>
			</TABLE>
